## Commenting Out the Update Functionality

To comment out the update functionality without removing the entire function, you can add `//` at the beginning of each line that you want to disable, like this:
```
// function tryApplyUpdates(onHotUpdateSuccess) {
//    ...
// }
```
This will make the function a no-op, disabling the update functionality without affecting the rest of your code.

## Generating a Commented-Out Version of the Code

If you want to generate a commented-out version of the code, you can use a regular expression to comment out the code. Here's how you can do it:
```
// console.log('trying to update');
//# sourceURL=webpack:///./main.js
(function (module) {
//  if (module.hot) {... (rest of the function)...
console.error('HotModuleReplacementPlugin is not in Webpack configuration.');
//# sourceMappingURL=main.js.map
```
You can search for the opening bracket `{` and the regular expression `// function\s\tryApplyUpdates\(.*?\)\s*\{` to comment out the function, or use a code editor with a `comment selection`

